definition:
A man of the tribe of Levi living at the time of Divided Monarchy, first mentioned at 1Ch.24.21; 
 son of: Rehabiah (H7345); 
 father of: Joram (H3141I); also called Jeshaiah at 1Ch.26.25; 
Another name of yish.shiy.yah (יִשִּׁיָּהוּ "Isshiah" H3449J)
 § Isaiah or Jesaiah or Jeshaiah = "Jehovah has saved"
1) son of Hananiah, brother of Pelatiah, and grandson of Zerubbabel
2) a Benjamite
3) son of Athaliah and chief of the house of Elam who returned with Ezra
4) a chief of the descendants of Merari who returned with Ezra
